modules.description: Provides functions to parse and generate protocol buffer build configurations, including handling .proto files and generating OCaml code. Works with structured data like file paths, build flags, and protocol buffer definitions. Used to automate the integration of protocol buffer compilation into OCaml build processes.

Provides functions to integrate Protocol Buffers compilation into OCamlbuild, including a `protoc` string constant for the compiler path, a `tag_protoc` function to tag generated files, and an `init` function to set up the build environment. Works with OCamlbuild's plugin types such as `Pathname.t` and `hook`. Used to automate generation of OCaml code from `.proto` files during the build process.
